SIGNED ARITHMETIC OVERFLOWS
ADDITION: Occurs if and only if 2 Two's Complement numbers are added and they both have the same sign (both positive or both negative) and the result has the opposite sign
SUBTRACTION: Occurs if and only if 2 Two's Complement numbers are subtracted, and their signs are different, and the result has the same sign as the subtrahend (the first one)
FLOATING POINT
$M \times 2^E$
M is the coefficient (aka, significand, fraction or mantissa)
E is the exponent (aka, characteristic)
No. of bits in exponent determines the range (big/smallness)
No. of bits in coefficient determines the precision (exactness)
