IEEE FLOATING POINT STANDARD - SINGLE PRECISION
Coefficient is called the significand in the IEEE standard
Value represented is $+/- 1.F \times 2^{(E-127)}$
The normal bit (the 1.) is omitted from the significand field $\rightarrow$ a hidden bit
Single precision yields 24 bits (approx. 7 decimal digits of precision)
